sentences.english: The labyrinths were supposed to confound any enemies who might get in.
sentences.chinese: 迷宫应该是为了迷惑入侵的敌人而建。

sentences.english: I always get lost in mazes.
If you love Labyrinth games, then Kingdom Skulls is for you.
sentences.chinese: 如果您喜欢迷宫游戏，这款骷髅王国是为你准备的。

sentences.english: And in this labyrinth where night is blind.
sentences.chinese: 在这连黑夜也目盲的迷宫中。

sentences.english: Enclosed rooms, mazes, and other barriers can also be constructed from wall sections.
sentences.chinese: 封闭房间，迷宫，和其他障碍，也可从墙上构造部分。

sentences.english: At present, Puzzle Patterns are the ultimate anti-corporate battle.
sentences.chinese: 目前，迷宫模式打响了最终反企业的战斗。

sentences.english: I believe my toy bear is hidden in this labyrinthic city.
sentences.chinese: 我相信迷宫一样的城市中藏着我童年的小熊。

sentences.english: He wandered through the labyrinth of the alleyways.
sentences.chinese: 他在迷宫似的小巷中闲逛。

sentences.english: The guide led us through the maze of caves.
sentences.chinese: 那个向导领我们穿过迷宫般的曲折洞穴。

sentences.english: Place O -ring into ID grooveofLabyrinth Rotor Sleeve.
sentences.chinese: 置O形圈于迷宫转子衬套内径槽内。

sentences.english: I twisted through a maze of narrow corridors.
sentences.chinese: 我弯弯曲曲地穿行迷宫式的狭窄走廊。

sentences.english: Ant colony algorithm is applied to maze problem in this paper.
sentences.chinese: 该文将蚁群算法应用于迷宫最优路径问题。

sentences.english: This particular valley is a maze of towers and outcroppings.
sentences.chinese: 这特殊的峡谷是一个由高塔和突出物构成的迷宫。

sentences.english: As a member of the mercenary group, the main character falls into a trap.
sentences.chinese: 身为佣兵团一员的主角，在进入迷宫后却中了陷阱。

sentences.english: Now he felt the cool breeze that was blowing in this part of the Maze and it was refreshing.
sentences.chinese: 这时，从迷宫中吹来习习的凉风，使人感到神清气爽。

sentences.english: They had solved the mystery of the maze.
sentences.chinese: 他们已经解开了迷宫之谜。
